dismissalText.commentary: Martin Guptill b Waller 105 (121b 9x4 0x6 168m) SR: 86.77

dismissalComment.html: is the fightback on? Fuller ball on the middle stump. Guptill comes forward and yorks himself as he is looking to force it away on the leg side. He has an exasperated expression at the end of it all. Waller has something to take back after the two dropped catches

dismissalText.commentary: Brendon McCullum c Sibanda b Meth 87 (99b 3x4 4x6 118m) SR: 87.87

dismissalComment.html: fifth time lucky for Zimbabwe! After letting off McCullum for four times, Sibanda holds a stunner at backward point by leaping to his left and getting hold of the ball with both his hands. The stint at NSW seems to have rubbed the Aussie superstitions on McCullum as he is dismissed for 87

dismissalText.commentary: BJ Watling run out (Meth) 19 (17b 3x4 0x6 19m) SR: 111.76

dismissalComment.html: how unfortunate can a batsman get? It is one thing to be dismissed if the ball  hits some part of the bowler and hits the stumps. It is quite another thing if the ball ricochets of your pad to the bowler and he whips the bails off. Expect to read about this dismissal in any kind of 'weird dismissal's list'. Unlucky Watling

commentTextItems.html: match and series for New Zealand as Oram turns it to fine-leg for a boundary

commentPostTextItems.html: It would have been interesting if any of Waller, Chigumbura or Masakadza held on to the chances offered to them by McCullum. It was not to be as the partnership between Guptill and McCullum sealed the match for New Zealand. Though Zimbabwe tried to force their way in at the end, the spinners let them down by bowling short and wide
Taylor would be a disappointed man as his centuries in consecutive matches did not see him on the winning side. He has a lot to figure out before the third ODI
Guptill is the Man of the match for his century
Please join us for the final ODI on Tuesday. Till then it's a good night from  all of us here

dismissalText.commentary: Rob Nicol c Mutizwa b Meth 9 (17b 0x4 0x6 31m) SR: 52.94

dismissalComment.html: full and down the leg side and Nicol gets a fine edge and an excellent catch from Mutizwa, quick work from the keeper.

dismissalText.commentary: Martin Guptill b Waller 105 (121b 9x4 0x6 168m) SR: 86.77

dismissalComment.html: is the fightback on? Fuller ball on the middle stump. Guptill comes forward and yorks himself as he is looking to force it away on the leg side. He has an exasperated expression at the end of it all. Waller has something to take back after the two dropped catches

dismissalText.commentary: Brendon McCullum c Sibanda b Meth 87 (99b 3x4 4x6 118m) SR: 87.87

dismissalComment.html: fifth time lucky for Zimbabwe! After letting off McCullum for four times, Sibanda holds a stunner at backward point by leaping to his left and getting hold of the ball with both his hands. The stint at NSW seems to have rubbed the Aussie superstitions on McCullum as he is dismissed for 87

headshotImage.caption: Forster Mutizwa player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Forster Mutizwa player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ross Taylor c Mutizwa b Utseya 11 (15b 1x4 0x6 14m) SR: 73.33

dismissalComment.html: gone! Short ball outside the off stump. Taylor chases the wide delivery and manages to get a faint edge. Mutizwa holds on and Utseya manages a wry smile. Too late in the day or do we have time enough for a Zimbabwean turnaround?

dismissalText.commentary: Kane Williamson not out 14 (18b 1x4 0x6 27m) SR: 77.77

dismissalText.commentary: BJ Watling run out (Meth) 19 (17b 3x4 0x6 19m) SR: 111.76

dismissalComment.html: how unfortunate can a batsman get? It is one thing to be dismissed if the ball  hits some part of the bowler and hits the stumps. It is quite another thing if the ball ricochets of your pad to the bowler and he whips the bails off. Expect to read about this dismissal in any kind of 'weird dismissal's list'. Unlucky Watling
